<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,832,1438]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Vertex, pronotum and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[605,733,906,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 20" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,326,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1424,323,1942]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 20. Dosal and lateral habitus and face. 1, 6, 11, 16: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 2, 7, 12, 17: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 3, 8, 13, 18: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 4, 9, 14, 19: T. quadragulatus sp. n.; 5, 10, 15, 20: T. luchunensis sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199897/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">Figs 3, 18</figureCitation>
) blackish brown, with yellowish brown longitudinal band extending from apex of vertex to posterior margin of scutellum medially; face yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1203,942,966]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 20" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,326,1940]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[164,1424,323,1942]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 20. Dosal and lateral habitus and face. 1, 6, 11, 16: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 2, 7, 12, 17: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 3, 8, 13, 18: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 4, 9, 14, 19: T. quadragulatus sp. n.; 5, 10, 15, 20: T. luchunensis sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199897/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[1172,1203,942,966]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
