</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,832,1438]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[374,458,1014,1038]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 45" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,178,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 45. Male genitalia. 21 – 25: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 26 – 30: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 31 – 35: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 36 – 40: quadragulatus sp. n.; 41 – 45: T. luchunensis sp. n.; 21, 26, 31, 36, 41: male pygofer, lateral view; 22, 27, 32, 37, 42: aedeagus, lateral view; 23, 28, 33, 38, 43: aedeagus, ventral view; 24, 29, 34, 39, 44: connective and style, dorsal view; 25, 30, 35, 40, 45: subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199898/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[429,458,1014,1038]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
) broad at base, slightly narrowed posteriorly with apex somewhat truncate in lateral view, macrosetae near dorsal and posterior margins very long. Apex of footlike apical process of style short and robust, about one sixth length of style (
<figureCitation box="[622,712,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 45" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,178,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 45. Male genitalia. 21 – 25: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 26 – 30: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 31 – 35: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 36 – 40: quadragulatus sp. n.; 41 – 45: T. luchunensis sp. n.; 21, 26, 31, 36, 41: male pygofer, lateral view; 22, 27, 32, 37, 42: aedeagus, lateral view; 23, 28, 33, 38, 43: aedeagus, ventral view; 24, 29, 34, 39, 44: connective and style, dorsal view; 25, 30, 35, 40, 45: subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199898/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[680,712,1086,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[928,1060,1086,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 45" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,178,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1889]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 45. Male genitalia. 21 – 25: T. bannaensis sp. n.; 26 – 30: T. fasciatus Li &amp; Wang; 31 – 35: T. flavifrons (Matsumura) comb. n.; 36 – 40: quadragulatus sp. n.; 41 – 45: T. luchunensis sp. n.; 21, 26, 31, 36, 41: male pygofer, lateral view; 22, 27, 32, 37, 42: aedeagus, lateral view; 23, 28, 33, 38, 43: aedeagus, ventral view; 24, 29, 34, 39, 44: connective and style, dorsal view; 25, 30, 35, 40, 45: subgenital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/199898/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="45">
Figs 
<number box="[989,1060,1086,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="45" value="32.5" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="32.0">32–33</number>
</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin concave medially; apex long and slender, extending distinctly beyond dorsal area of lamellate lateral process of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
